  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Cut the&nbsp;<strong>potatoes</strong>&nbsp;(skins on) into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong>, then toss them gently to coat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Place the tray in the oven until step 4 (approx. 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/hazelnut-crusted-pork-tenderloin/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic </strong></p>\r\n<p>Strip the<strong> rosemary</strong> leaves from the stalks and chop finely</p>\r\n<p>Grind the <strong>hazelnuts&nbsp;</strong>in a<strong> pestle &amp; mortar</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>rosemary</strong>, <strong>ground hazelnuts</strong> and <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> to a mixing bowl with&nbsp;2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil </strong>&amp; season with a large pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Melt 40g <span class=\"text-danger\">[80g]</span>&nbsp;<strong>butter</strong> in a pan and once melted, add it to the <strong>nut mixture</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/hazelnut-crusted-pork-tenderloin/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat the <strong>pork tenderloin's</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Add the pork to the<strong> nut mixture</strong></p>\r\n<p>Use your hands to firmly press the nut mixture onto the tenderloins so they're&nbsp;fully coated &ndash; this is your <strong>hazelnut crusted pork&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/hazelnut-crusted-pork-tenderloin/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place the<strong> hazelnut crusted</strong>&nbsp;<strong>pork</strong>&nbsp;and any spare <strong>nut&nbsp;mixture</strong>&nbsp;over the potatoes</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the pork&nbsp;is cooked and the potatoes are crispy&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/hazelnut-crusted-pork-tenderloin/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skin on) finely, discarding the core<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></p>\r\n<p>Peel and slice the <strong>red</strong>&nbsp;<strong>onion</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> into&nbsp;thin wedges</p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme</strong> leaves from the stalks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>and once melted, add the <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>apple</strong>, <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion</strong> and<strong> sultanas</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>and cook&nbsp;for 10-15 min or until coloured&nbsp;and softened</p>\r\n<p>Boil a&nbsp;kettle&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/hazelnut-crusted-pork-tenderloin/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>spring greens</strong>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p>Bring a large pot of <strong>salted boiled water</strong> to the boil over a high heat, and once boiling, add the <strong>spring greens</strong>&nbsp;and cook&nbsp;for 3 min or until tender, then drain and return them to the pot</p>\r\n<p>Transfer the cooked<strong> pork</strong> to a chopping board, cover with a tea towel &amp; leave to rest for 5 min, returning the potatoes to the oven until serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/hazelnut-crusted-pork-tenderloin/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>sugar</strong> to the softened apples and cook for 2 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>flour</strong> to the pan and cook for a further min <span class=\"text-highlight\">&ndash;</span> this will thicken them a little&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Whisk 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>water</strong> into the pan, bring the pan to a boil, then remove it from the heat</p>\r\n<p>Stir in the <strong>thyme</strong> leaves and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/hazelnut-crusted-pork-tenderloin/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the rested<strong> hazelnut crusted pork</strong>&nbsp;and serve it over the <strong>balsamic apples</strong> with the crispy <strong>potatoes</strong> and <strong>spring greens</strong> to the side</p>\r\n<p>Scatter over any lose crumbs!</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
